body: @liuziyue Could you please take a look and confirm whether 4fd9fef9ee04c0844d679e81264779402cfa445c has changed the behavior here? Thanks!
@brosenfi, could you share an onnx model that could reproduce the issue?

Hi @tianleiwu - I'm going to have to confirm with others at my company whether it's allowed (may take a few days).  Also this is a huge file of course with all the weights (~ 1.3GB) - is there metadata that I could produce instead of uploading the huge file that would be useful for reproducing?

@brosenfi, you can export the onnx model with external data format (use --large_model in tf2onnx). In that format, graph and weights are stored in separated files. The graph (.onnx file) is very small and I think it is enough for investigation, and you need not share the weights.

Thanks for the tip @tianleiwu - I tried doing this a little bit ago but ran into a couple of problems - first off the input we use to tf2onnx is not a saved model, which apparently is required - we are instead freezing the saved model first with a call to tf.graph_util.convert_variables_to_constants .  The other issue is that is requires a TF 2.x model - ours is TF 1.x .

However - I still can convert the graph to "external data" using onnx itself (thankfully this is now available as of version 1.9.0 = https://github.com/onnx/onnx/blob/master/docs/ExternalData.md ).  I will get you this file shortly.

Have two PRs related to the model:
(1) Fix symbolic shape inference for Unsqueeze of opset 13: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/7555
(2) Catch exception in shape inference and clean up prune graph: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/7560

After these changes, optimizer could run on the model. However, attention can not be fused since mask is different. A possible fix is to add a new pattern for mask subgraph like https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/d7b84e67fe0be3be9d680331005e59b278511f13/onnxruntime/python/tools/transformers/onnx_model_bert_tf.py#L45-L49.

This issue has been automatically marked as stale due to inactivity and will be closed in 7 days if no further activity occurs. If further support is needed, please provide an update and/or more details.
